Book of Hours, Use of Rome

Free Library of Philadelphia, Lewis E 112. France, First quarter 16th century. This manuscript is an early sixteenth-century Book of Hours with a liturgical calendar for Lyon. It is generously illuminated, with twelve full-page miniatures, eighteen smaller miniatures, and illuminated initials. At least five leaves are missing from the manuscript.
